Poland international Arkadiusz Milik’s future at Napoli is yet to be decided as reports claim that there is no updates of a potential contract extension. According to Calciomercato, Napoli are looking for ways to release the player to another club in a bid to attract new signings and bolster the squad. READ ALSO: Ashley Young agree to one-year contract extension at Inter Sportilita in Italy claims that the Serie A side has placed a €50m for the clubs who will be interested in making a move for Milik. Furthermore, Juventus and AC Milan have emerged as potential suitors for the striker’s signature and it is yet to be seen which of the teams will be approaching Napoli with an offer. 